	(115,'It\'s okay to speed','/audio/crazies/2018/09/07/GQZr3JJ7AUpwB1f2P6Sz5b929e57d9daf.mp3',1,1,1,'2018-09-07 22:50:47','2019-10-02 01:53:25',4,NULL,NULL),
	(116,'It\'s okay to speed','/audio/crazies/2018/09/09/8TIfk4gemg7jbBe791Tp5b9488c21e31d.mp3',1,1,1,'2018-09-09 09:43:14','2019-10-02 01:53:25',4,'/images/crazy_courses/2019/10/02/0hdqDnnP5d93f09ba6001.jpg','I am sick of hearing people say that it is OK to drive 10 or 15 mph above the posted speed LIMIT.\r\nLook up the definition of LIMIT, and I’m sure it won’t say anything about speeds ABOVE the posted LIMIT. Maybe newer cars are safer at higher speeds, but not all the cars that speeders drive are new. Maybe the experience of the driver and his vision, reaction time, or other issues may not be the same as the BEST driver on the road. Maybe the INFRASTRUCTURE of the country is crumbling, but speeders think all roads are safe at any speed.\r\nThere is clearly something wrong. As with other laws, if YOU disagree with a law, contact your lawmaking officials and work to get it CHANGED. YOU have no right to raise the legal limit for your own selfish reasons. I do not want to get a ticket, pay money for it, and possibly endanger MY license just because there are idiots on the road who think they know it all. I also do not want to be killed in an accident caused by the know-it-all guy who was tailgating me when a deer jumped in front of me or when a child ran across the road or when I got a flat tire caused by some litterbug who threw something dangerous onto the road.\r\nHorror stories abound. Let’s not break the law. There are reasons those laws exist. If someone tells me that cops won’t bother you for going up to 10 mph above the legal LIMIT (there’s that word again), I would probably be the one ticketed for doing 5 mph above the limit.\r\nI also don’t want to hear all the stupid arguments about non-speeders “obstructing the flow of traffic.” If you are in such a hurry, PLAN AHEAD, and leave earlier for your destination.'),
	(117,'Check your tires','/audio/crazies/2018/09/10/b3sD1ODRkTWHUA6qz8x85b9679e494a73.mp3',1,1,1,'2018-09-10 21:04:20','2019-10-02 01:53:25',4,'/images/crazy_courses/2019/10/02/4I0GK2415d93f03dbd0c4.jpg','How to Check Your Tires\r\nCheck Tread Depth\r\n\r\nEvaluate the tread depth of your tires to make sure you have enough traction to grip the road. The penny test is a simple way to do this. Just place a penny upside down in your tread. If you can see the top of Lincoln’s head, it may be time for new tires.'),
	(118,'Don\'t be in a hurry','/audio/crazies/2018/09/10/e1PqtgNe8iGpTErQgTbZ5b967dccf159e.mp3',1,1,1,'2018-09-10 21:21:00','2019-10-02 01:53:25',4,'/images/crazy_courses/2019/10/02/7PYV9XzZ5d93efeeb1beb.jpg','Consider that we want to say a sentence with meaning in negative form of \"hurry up!\". Which one is true?\r\n\r\nDon\'t be in a hurry\r\nDon\'t be hurry'),
